much faster. For obvious reasons we'd like to ask you to not disclose this issue to any other party.","automated_response":true,"created_at":"2016-09-02T18:16:33.081Z","updated_at":"2016-09-02T18:16:33.081Z","actor":{"url":"/nextcloud","ibb":false,"profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/013/291/68f57538488b5716cdeeb6b78955f9e46685bc09_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"profile":{"name":"Nextcloud"}},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"nextcloud","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1170368,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugNeedsMoreInfo","message":"Thanks a lot for your report, much appreciated. Some clarification requests below :)\n\nAt the moment the implementation is as following: Removing a session will remove the PHP session itself. But in the case of the desktop client a new one will created on the next request (using username + password). It is thus only really useful for the scenario where the user has changed their password and wants to revoke old sessions. But in fact, this needs a UI refinement.\n\nCan you let us know how you logged-in on the desktop client? Did you use an application specific password or password and user name?\n\n\u003e 4) Though android client is still active, sessions are not capturing in personal --\u003e sessions tab\n\nSo the Android client is never displayed at all?","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-09-02T18:54:01.540Z","updated_at":"2016-09-02T18:54:01.540Z","actor":{"username":"lukasreschke","cleared":false,"url":"/lukasreschke","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/037/891/e7fea4d5383dc07d1fe767b02f3bda2bc7639c63_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"nextcl